qas.question: What is the Italian term for the prime minister?

answers.text: president of the council of ministers

qas.question: What is the native term for prime minister in Scandinavia?
What does the title Satsminister refer to in Italy?

plausible_answers.text: the head of government of subnational entities such as provinces

qas.question: Who is nown as the prime minister in federations?

context: Other common forms include <a0_0>president of the council of ministers<a0_0/> (for example in Italy, <b2_0>Presidente del Consiglio dei Ministri<b2_0/>), President of the Executive Council, or Minister-President. In the Scandinavian countries the prime minister is called <a1_0>statsminister<a1_0/> in the native languages (i.e. minister of state). In federations, <b3_0>the head of government of subnational entities such as provinces<b3_0/> is most commonly known as the premier, chief minister, governor or minister-president.
